Defining mean of PA1 optimization problem (target of PA1).

In [ ]:
class pa1_mean(ElementwiseProblem):

    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__(n_var=3, # numero de parametros
                         n_obj=1, # numero de funcoes objetivos
                         n_constr=1, # numero de restricoes
                         xl=np.array([-(2**3)**0.25, -(2**3)**0.25, -(2**3)**0.25]),
                         xu=np.array([(2**3)**0.25, (2**3)**0.25, (2**3)**0.25])
                         )

    def _evaluate(self, x, out, *args, **kwargs):
      # funcao objetivo
      meanpa1 = b0 + np.matmul(np.transpose([x[0],x[1],x[2]]),b) + np.matmul(np.matmul(np.transpose([x[0],x[1],x[2]]),B),[x[0],x[1],x[2]])
            
      # restricao
      g1 = x[0]**2 + x[1]**2 + x[2]**2 - ((2**3)**0.25)**2
      
      out['F'] = [meanpa1]
      out['G'] = [g1]

problem_pa1_mean = pa1_mean()

Definition of the three-objective problem of PA1, PA2, and PA3.

In [ ]:
class tri_obj(ElementwiseProblem):

    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__(n_var=3, # numero de parametros
                         n_obj=3, # numero de funcoes objetivos
                         n_constr=1, # numero de restricoes
                         xl=np.array([-(2**3)**0.25, -(2**3)**0.25, -(2**3)**0.25]),
                         xu=np.array([(2**3)**0.25, (2**3)**0.25, (2**3)**0.25])
                         )

    def _evaluate(self, x, out, *args, **kwargs):
      # funcoes objetivo
      rmse1 = ((b0 + np.matmul(np.transpose([x[0],x[1],x[2]]),b) + np.matmul(np.matmul(np.transpose([x[0],x[1],x[2]]),B),[x[0],x[1],x[2]]) - TT)**2 + (mse + np.matmul(np.transpose(g + np.matmul(np.transpose(D),[x[0],x[1],x[2]])), (g + np.matmul(np.transpose(D),[x[0],x[1],x[2]])))))**0.5
      rmse2 = ((b02 + np.matmul(np.transpose([x[0],x[1],x[2]]),b2) + np.matmul(np.matmul(np.transpose([x[0],x[1],x[2]]),B2),[x[0],x[1],x[2]]) - TT2)**2 + (mse2 + np.matmul(np.transpose(g2 + np.matmul(np.transpose(D2),[x[0],x[1],x[2]])), (g2 + np.matmul(np.transpose(D2),[x[0],x[1],x[2]])))))**0.5
      rmse3 = ((b03 + np.matmul(np.transpose([x[0],x[1],x[2]]),b3) + np.matmul(np.matmul(np.transpose([x[0],x[1],x[2]]),B3),[x[0],x[1],x[2]]) - TT3)**2 + (mse3 + np.matmul(np.transpose(g3 + np.matmul(np.transpose(D3),[x[0],x[1],x[2]])), (g3 + np.matmul(np.transpose(D3),[x[0],x[1],x[2]])))))**0.5
      
      # restricao
      g1 = x[0]**2 + x[1]**2 + x[2]**2 - ((2**3)**0.25)**2
      
      out['F'] = [rmse1, rmse2, rmse3]
      out['G'] = [g1]

problem_tri_obj = tri_obj()

Defining the four objective problem. It is important to do that without run the three objective problem.

In [ ]:
class four_obj(ElementwiseProblem):

    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__(n_var=3, # numero de parametros
                         n_obj=4, # numero de funcoes objetivos
                         n_constr=1, # numero de restricoes
                         xl=np.array([-(2**3)**0.25, -(2**3)**0.25, -(2**3)**0.25]),
                         xu=np.array([(2**3)**0.25, (2**3)**0.25, (2**3)**0.25])
                         )

    def _evaluate(self, x, out, *args, **kwargs):
      # funcoes objetivo
      rmse1 = ((b0 + np.matmul(np.transpose([x[0],x[1],x[2]]),b) + np.matmul(np.matmul(np.transpose([x[0],x[1],x[2]]),B),[x[0],x[1],x[2]]) - TT)**2 + (mse + np.matmul(np.transpose(g + np.matmul(np.transpose(D),[x[0],x[1],x[2]])), (g + np.matmul(np.transpose(D),[x[0],x[1],x[2]])))))**0.5
      rmse2 = ((b02 + np.matmul(np.transpose([x[0],x[1],x[2]]),b2) + np.matmul(np.matmul(np.transpose([x[0],x[1],x[2]]),B2),[x[0],x[1],x[2]]) - TT2)**2 + (mse2 + np.matmul(np.transpose(g2 + np.matmul(np.transpose(D2),[x[0],x[1],x[2]])), (g2 + np.matmul(np.transpose(D2),[x[0],x[1],x[2]])))))**0.5
      rmse3 = ((b03 + np.matmul(np.transpose([x[0],x[1],x[2]]),b3) + np.matmul(np.matmul(np.transpose([x[0],x[1],x[2]]),B3),[x[0],x[1],x[2]]) - TT3)**2 + (mse3 + np.matmul(np.transpose(g3 + np.matmul(np.transpose(D3),[x[0],x[1],x[2]])), (g3 + np.matmul(np.transpose(D3),[x[0],x[1],x[2]])))))**0.5
      MRR = -250*4*(18**3/(8*10))*(x[2]*(65-35)/2 + 50)*(((x[0]*(0.2-0.1)/2 + 0.15)*10**-3)/(x[1]*(0.2-0.1)/2 + 0.15))*((((x[0]*(0.2-0.1)/2 + 0.15)*0.001)**2 + ((x[1]*(0.2-0.1)/2 + 0.15)*8/18)**2)**0.5)

      # restricao
      g1 = x[0]**2 + x[1]**2 + x[2]**2 - ((2**3)**0.25)**2
      
      out['F'] = [rmse1, rmse2, rmse3, MRR]
      out['G'] = [g1]

problem_four_obj = four_obj()

n_evals = []

    feas = np.where(opt.get("feasible"))[0]
